20ISRO's%20future%20moon%20missions%2C%20including%20Chandrayaan%204.%20It%20is%20also%20particularly%20important%20for%20India's%20plan%20to%20set%20up%20its%20own%20space%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%20this%20year%2C%20the%20government%20had%20announced%20that%20India%20will%20have%20its%20own%20Space%20Station%20called%20the%20Bharatiya%20Antriksh%20Station%20by%202035.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22ISROs%20PSLV-C60%20carrying%20SpaDeX%20and%20its%20payloads%2C%20lifts%20off%20from%20the%20first%20launch%20pad%20at%20Satish%20Dhawan%20Space%20Centre%2C%20in%20Sriharikota%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22ISROs%20PSLV-C60%20carrying%20SpaDeX%20and%20its%20payloads%2C%20lifts%20off%20from%20the%20first%20launch%20pad%20at%20Satish%20Dhawan%20Space%20Centre%2C%20in%20Sriharikota%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fhug8kt8o_isro-pslv-c60-spadex-mission-and-poem-4-mission-pti_625x300_30_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Csmall%3E%3Cem%3EISRO's%20PSLV-C60%20carrying%20SpaDeX%20and%20its%20payloads%2C%20lifts%20off%20from%20the%20first%20launch%20pad%20at%20Satish%20Dhawan%20Space%20Centre%2C%20in%20Sriharikota%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsmall%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20there%20are%20two%20other%20space%20stations%20-%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%2C%20built%20by%20the%20United%20States%20(NASA)%20and%20Russia%20(Roscosmos).%20The%20US%20side%20of%20the%20ISS%20is%20built%20by%20NASA%20and%20European%20Space%20Agency%20or%20ESA.%20The%20second%20space%20station%20is%20being%20built%20by%20China%2C%20and%20is%20called%20the%20Tiangong%20Space%20Station.%20India%20aims%20to%20set%20up%20the%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20time%20astronauts%20or%20cosmonauts%20are%20sent%20to%20space%2C%20especially%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%2C%20the%20shuttle%20or%20capsule%20they%20travel%20in%20needs%20to%20perform%20a%20docking%20manoeuvre.%20Only%20after%20the%20docking%20procedure%20is%20complete%2C%20and%20the%20two%20objects%20are%20securely%20interlocked%2C%20can%20the%20astronauts%20get%20into%20the%20pressurised%20cabin%20of%20the%20space%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EISRO'S%20DOCKING%20EXPERIMENT%20EXPLAINED%20WITH%20THE%20HELP%20OF%20%3Cem%3E'INTERSTELLAR'%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDocking%20in%20space%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20difficult%20and%20complicated%20procedures%20-%20the%20slightest%20of%20errors%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20catastrophe%20-%20an%20example%20of%20which%20was%20shown%20in%20the%20epic%20sci-fi%20movie%20Interstellar%20-%20where%20Cooper%20and%20the%20crew%20had%20to%20navigate%20a%20near-impossible%20and%20heart-pounding%20docking%20scenario%20after%20a%20minuscule%20error%20by%20Dr%20Mann%20sends%20the%20Endurance%20space%20station%20into%20an%20uncontrolled%20spin%20due%20to%20a%20catastrophic%20decompression.%20The%20scene%20highlights%20a%20complex%20docking%20manoeuvre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FonVhbeY7nLM%3Fsi%3D2q9iFQnLltCL84ls%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20like%20in%20the%20movie%2C%20where%20there%20was%20a%20Lander%20spacecraft%20and%20a%20Courier%20spacecraft%2C%20ISRO's%20mission%20has%20two%20spaceships%20-%20the%20Chaser%20(SDX01)%20and%20the%20Target%20(SDX02)%2C%20each%20weighing%20220%20kilograms.%20As%20the%20names%20suggest%2C%20the%20aim%20of%20the%20mission%20will%20be%20for%20the%20chaser%20to%20chase%20the%20target%20while%20both%20are%20orbiting%20Earth%20at%20a%20high%20speed%20and%20dock%20with%20it%20expeditiously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EALL%20ABOUT%20ISRO'S%20SPADEX%20MISSION%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SpaDex%20mission%20lift-off%20at%202200%20hrs%20(10%20pm)%20IST%20on%20December%2030%20from%20the%20Satish%20Dhawan%20Space%20Centre%20in%20Sriharikota%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EISRO's%20launch%20was%20onboard%20the%20workhorse%20PSLV-C60%20rocket%2C%20which%20put%20the%20two%20spacecraft%20in%20low-Earth%20orbit%2C%20roughly%20475%20km%20above%20the%20Earth's%20surface.%20The%20inclination%20of%20the%20two%20spacecraft%20will%20be%20at%2055%20degrees%20facing%20the%20Earth.%20After%20being%20deployed%20in%20a%20circular%20orbit%2C%20the%20two%20spacecraft%20will%20grow%20apart%20by%20around%2020%20kilometers%20over%2024%20hours.%20The%20scientists%20will%20first%20carry%20out%20several%20other%20experiments%20under%20the%20POEM-4%20mission%20-%20a%20parallel%20mission%20to%20SpaDex%20(explained%20below).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fembed-player%2F%3Fsite%3Dclassic%26id%3D882122%26autostart%3Dfalse%26autoplay%3D0%26pWidth%3D500%26pHeight%3D281%26category%3Dembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20sitting%20at%20ISRO's%20mission%20control%20in%20Bengaluru%20are%20expected%20to%20initiate%20the%20intricate%20and%20precise%20docking%20and%20undocking%20manoeuvre%20in%20the%20later%20half%20of%20the%20first%20week%20of%20January.%20If%20successful%2C%20India%20will%20create%20history%20by%20becoming%20only%20the%20fourth%20nation%20in%20the%20world%20to%20possess%20such%20technological%20ability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EAccording%20to%20ISRO%2C%20the%20main%20objectives%20of%20the%20SpaDeX%20mission%20include%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETo%20develop%20and%20demonstrate%20the%20technology%20needed%20for%20rendezvous%2C%20docking%2C%20and%20undocking%20of%20two%20small%20spacecraft.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20demonstration%20of%20the%20transfer%20of%20electric%20power%20between%20the%20docked%20spacecraft%2C%20which%20is%20essential%20for%20future%20applications%20such%20as%20in-space%20robotics.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EComposite%20spacecraft%20control%2C%20including%20remotely%20controlling%20it%20both%20in%20space%20and%20from%20mission%20control.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPayload%20operations%20after%20undocking.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20mission%20is%20crucial%20for%20India's%20ability%20to%20set%20up%20its%20own%20Space%20Station.%20It%20will%20also%20give%20India's%20RLV%20or%20Reusable%20Launch%20Vehicle%20-%20India's%20variant%20of%20NASA's%20iconic%20space%20shuttle%20-%20docking%20capability%20in%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fen3bvdoo_isro-rlv-ians_625x300_24_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Csmall%3E%3Cem%3EIndia's%20Reusable%20Launch%20Vehicle%20or%20RLV%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsmall%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHOW%20THE%20INTERNATIONAL%20SPACE%20STATION%20WAS%20BUILT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20key%20missions%2C%20NASA's%20space%20shuttle%20was%20used%20by%20the%20United%20States%20to%20construct%20the%20US%20side%20of%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%20Russia%20too%20used%20their%20own%20space%20shuttle%20to%20build%20the%20Russian%20side%20of%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%20While%20NASA%20had%20a%20series%20of%20space%20shuttles%2C%20starting%20with%20Columbia%20and%20evolving%20into%20Challenger%2C%20Discovery%2C%20Atlantis%2C%20and%20Endeavour%2C%20Russian%20space%20agency%20Roscosmos%20named%20their%20space%20shuttle%20Buran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22NASAs%20Space%20Shuttle%20(L)%20and%20Russias%20Space%20Shuttle%20(R)%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22NASAs%20Space%20Shuttle%20(L)%20and%20Russias%20Space%20Shuttle%20(R)%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F3ip2c4io_russia-space-shuttle-buran_625x300_24_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Csmall%3E%3Cem%3ENASA's%20Space%20Shuttle%20(L)%20and%20Russia's%20Space%20Shuttle%20(R)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsmall%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20insightful%20video%20of%20how%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20-%20the%20largest%20man-made%20space%20object%20-%20was%20built%20by%20the%20US%20and%20Russian%20space%20shuttles%20using%20the%20docking%20mechanism%20and%20robotic%20arms%20in%20addition%20to%20astronauts%20and%20cosmonauts%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FFhKOuxhGlmI%3Fsi%3D4EMigwU32KX2MJB1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EISRO'S%20POEM-4%20MISSION%20-%20AND%20EXPERIMENT%20WITH%20MICROGRAVITY%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20space%20docking%20manoeuvre%2C%20there%20is%20another%20key%20mission%20objective.%20ISRO%20plans%20to%20experiment%20with%20microgravity%20during%20the%20PSLV%20rocket's%20fourth-stage.%20ISRO%20aims%20to%20use%20the%20spent%20fourth%20stage%2C%20which%20it%20has%20termed%20POEM-4%20or%20PSLV%20Orbital%20Experimental%20Module%204%2C%20as%20a%20platform%20for%20carrying%20our%20experiments%20with%20microgravity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F0o02p884_isro-pslv-stage-4_625x300_24_December_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20space%20agency%2C%20it%20provides%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20scientific%20community%20to%20carry%20out%20certain%20in-orb