id.%20Trump%20would%20have%20to%20explain%20to%20the%20full%20Second%20Circuit%20why%20the%20issues%20are%20so%20important%2C%20and%20the%20three-judge%20panel's%20decision%20is%20so%20profoundly%20wrong%20that%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20overturned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20case%20like%20this%2C%20it%20could%20take%20a%20few%20months%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20full%20panel%20to%20consider%20Trump's%20petition%20and%20any%20response%20they%20allow%20from%20Carroll's%20side%2C%20and%20then%20vote%20on%20whether%20to%20hear%20the%20case%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%20appeal%2C%20there%20were%20only%20basic%20legal%20questions%20in%20dispute%2C%20meaning%20how%20the%20law%20was%20applied%2C%20and%20the%20three-judge%20panel's%20review%20was%20limited%20to%20looking%20for%20an%20abuse%20of%20discretion%2C%26quot%3B%20Paridis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20will%20seek%20review%20from%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20next%2C%20Paradis%20predicted.%20The%20president-elect%20selected%20three%20of%20the%20nine%20justices%20in%20his%20first%20term.%20He%20could%20place%20more%20justices%20on%20the%20bench%20by%20the%20time%20oral%20arguments%20would%20take%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20president-elect%20would%20first%20have%20to%20ask%20the%20high%20court%20to%20hear%20his%20appeal%2C%20and%20that%20process%20could%20keep%20the%20Carroll%20judgment%20frozen%20well%20into%20next%20year%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSCOTUS%20would%20likely%20not%20decide%20to%20hear%20the%20case%20until%20the%20end%20of%20next%20September%20at%20the%20earliest%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20who%20will%20be%20on%20Trump's%20legal%20team%20if%20he%20continues%20to%20appeal%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-appeal-e-jean-carroll-sexual-abuse-case-plane-law-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohn%20Sauer%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20presented%20the%20oral%20argument%20before%20the%20Second%20Circuit%2C%20was%20designated%20by%20Trump%20to%20serve%20as%20the%20Justice%20Department%20Solicitor%20General%20in%20his%20next%20presidential%20term.%20Other%20attorneys%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20case%2C%20including%20Todd%20Blanche%2C%20Emil%20Bove%2C%20and%20Alina%20Habba%2C%20are%20set%20to%20serve%20other%20posts%20in%20the%20Justice%20Department%20or%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonday's%20decision%20is%20for%20one%20of%20two%20separate%20civil%20lawsuits%20E.%20Jean%20Carroll%20brought%20against%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20trial%20took%20place%20in%20January%202024%2C%20and%20concerned%20additional%20defamation%20damages%20over%20Trump%20disparaging%20Carroll%20and%20calling%20her%20a%20liar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20in%20that%20case%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trial-verdict-e-jean-carroll-defamation-damages-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eawarded%20Carroll%20%2483.3%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Trump%20is%20appealing%20that%20case%2C%20too%2C%20with%20a%20process%20that%20is%20running%20on%20a%20separate%20track.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonday's%20appellate%20court%20decision%20largely%20focused%20on%20whether%20it%20was%20appropriate%20for%20US%20District%20Judge%20Lewis%20Kaplan%2C%20the%20trial%20judge%2C%20to%20allow%20certain%20types%20of%20evidence%20to%20be%20seen%20by%20the%20jurors%20who%20held%20Trump%20liable%20for%20sexually%20abusing%20Carroll.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20lawyers%20argued%20Kaplan%20should%20not%20have%20shown%20jurors%20the%20%26quot%3BAccess%20Hollywood%26quot%3B%20tape%2C%20where%20Trump%20bragged%20about%20grabbing%20women%20by%20the%20genitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20jury%20could%20have%20reasonably%20concluded%20from%20those%20statements%20that%2C%20in%20the%20past%2C%20Mr.%20Trump%20had%20kissed%20women%20without%20their%20consent%20and%20then%20proceeded%20to%20touch%20their%20genitalia%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20attorneys%20had%20also%20argued%20it%20was%20inappropriate%20to%20allow%20testimony%20from%20Natasha%20Stoynoff%20and%20Jessica%20Leeds%2C%20two%20other%20women%20who%20had%20accused%20Trump%20of%20sexual%20misconduct.%20The%20Second%20Circuit%20judges%20agreed%20with%20Kaplan%2C%20ruling%20that%20their%20stories%20helped%20establish%20a%20pattern%20of%20conduct%20from%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20jury%20could%20reasonably%20infer%20from%20Ms.%20Stoynoff's%20testimony%20and%20the%20Access%20Hollywood%20tape%20that%20Mr.%20Trump%20engaged%20in%20similar%20conduct%20with%20other%20women%20%E2%80%94%20a%20pattern%20of%20abrupt%2C%20nonconsensual%2C%20and%20physical%20advances%20on%20women%20he%20barely%20knew%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judges%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-loses-e-jean-carroll-appeal-30-days-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735582124000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64555ec5bcb4870018c7fcea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-loses-e-jean-carroll-appeal-30-days-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20appeals%20court%20upheld%20a%20jury%20verdict%20finding%20Donald%20Trump%20liable%20for%20sexually%20abusing%20and%20defaming%20E.%20Jean%20Carroll.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jshamsian%40businessinsider.com%20(Jacob%20Shamsian%2CLaura%20Italiano)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A151%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-loses-e-jean-carroll-appeal-30-days-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Underreported%20and%20undercovered'%3A%20CBS%20reporter%20slams%20media%20coverage%20of%20Biden's%20'cognitive%20decline'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735582081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-116807