ed%20By%20Ex-India%20Star%20On%20Jaiswal%20DRS%20Row%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFormer%20India%20wicketkeeper-batter%20Surinder%20Khanna%20lashed%20out%20at%20India's%20approach%20in%20the%20fourth%20Test%20against%20Australia%20and%20called%20for%20'fair%20play'%20from%20the%20visiting%20side%20following%20their%20184-run%20defeat%20at%20Melbourne%20Cricket%20Ground%20on%20Monday.%20Chasing%20340%20on%20the%20final%20day%20of%20the%20match%2C%20Indian%20batters%20once%20again%20faltered%20against%20Australia's%20bowling%20attack%20as%20the%20hosts%20took%202-1%20lead%20in%20the%20five-Test%20Border-Gavaskar%20Trophy%20series.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20India's%20chase%2C%20India%20opener%20Yashasvi%20Jaiswal's%20dismissal%20became%20the%20hot%20topic%20of%20debate%20after%20third%20umpire%20Sharfuddoula%20Saikat%20overturned%20on-field%20umpire%20Joel%20Wilson's%20decision%20without%20any%20conclusive%20evidence.%20Despite%20no%20disturbance%20on%20the%20Snickometer%20when%20the%20ball%20hit%20Jaiswal's%20gloves%2C%20the%20video%20evidence%2C%20however%2C%20showed%20some%20deflection%20based%20on%20which%20third%20umpire%20made%20his%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20was%20not%20taken%20well%20by%20the%20Indian%20camp%20and%20also%20by%20former%20players%20as%20they%20criticised%20the%20technology%20for%20not%20fulfilling%20the%20purpose%20completely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Khanna%20had%20a%20different%20take%20on%20that%20and%20suggested%20'there's%20no%20point%20in%20making%20controversy'.%20He%20advised%20Rohit%20Sharma-led%20team%20to%20play%20fair%20cricket%20first%20to%20change%20the%20result%20of%20the%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20point%20in%20making%20controversy%2C%20they've%20shown%20it%20from%20four%20angles%20that%20the%20ball%20hit%20the%20gloves%20and%20its%20pace%20also%20decreased%20before%20Alex%20Carey%20caught%20it%20behind%20the%20stumps.%20Akash%20Deep%20also%20complained%20of%20a%20similar%20thing%20when%20he%20was%20caught%20out.%20'Juthe%20log%20hai%20yeh%20(they%20are%20all%20liars)'%2C%20you%20have%20to%20play%20fair%20wicket%20first%20then%20only%20you'll%20start%20winning.%20When%20the%20bat%20is%20in%20your%20hand%2C%20how%20can%20you%20not%20know%20about%20edging%20the%20ball%3F%20We%20have%20played%20bad%20and%20we%20have%20lost.%20What%20kind%20of%20batting%20they're%20doing%3F%20Come%20the%20IPL%2C%20these%20players%20will%20hit%20runs.%20Don't%20play%20over-aggressive%20T20%20cricket%20and%20play%20positively.%20Let's%20hope%20that%20the%20luck%20changes%20in%20the%20New%20Year%20(for%20the%20Indian%20team)%2C%26quot%3B%20Khanna%20told%20IANS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20defeat%20in%20Melbourne%2C%20India's%20point%20percentage%20(PCT)%2C%20however%2C%20has%20dipped%20from%2055.88%20to%2052.78%20while%20Australia's%20PCT%20saw%20a%20jump%20from%2058.89%20to%2061.46%20as%20they%20close%20in%20on%20a%20second%20consecutive%20appearance%20in%20the%20WTC%20final.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20on%20Sunday%2C%20South%20Africa%20became%20the%20first%20team%20to%20qualify%20for%20next%20year's%20WTC%20final%20at%20Lord's.%20Defending%20champions%20Australia%20need%20just%20one%20win%20in%20their%20remaining%20three%20Tests%20(one%20against%20India%20and%20two%20against%20Sri%20Lanka)%20to%20secure%20their%20second%20consecutive%20final%20appearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20however%2C%20can%20still%20qualify%20for%20the%20WTC%20final%20but%20they%20must%20win%20the%20final%20Test%20of%20the%20series%20against%20Australia%20in%20Sydney%20to%20tie%20the%20Border-Gavaskar%20series%20and%20then%20rely%20on%20the%20Aussies%20not%20winning%20a%20Test%20during%20their%20series%20in%20Sri%20Lanka%20that%20commences%20next%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22p